16 Section 2. Section 44-4-1505, MCA, is amended to read:
17 "44-4-1505. (Temporary) Emergency lodging and recovery program for victims of domestic
18 violence or human trafficking -- grants reimbursement -- rulemaking -- definitions. (1) There is an
19 emergency lodging and recovery program for licensed establishments located in the state to assist designated
20 organizations in providing short-term lodging and recovery assistance in the state to individuals and families
21 that are victims of domestic violence or human trafficking.
22 (2) (a) Subject to the provisions of this section, participating establishments may submit a grant
23 application to enroll in the emergency lodging and recovery program. Participating establishments may seek
24 reimbursement from the department of justice for providing emergency lodging and recovery assistance to an
25 individual or family who is in immediate need of shelter based on being a victim of domestic violence or human
26 trafficking.
27 (b) In order to be eligible for the grant reimbursement, the individual or family must be referred to
28 the establishment by a designated organization.
